{"TopicId":198446,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"Recommend a security system","CreatedByName":"MaximilianIV","CreatedById":194147,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-01T01:34:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MaximilianIV","CreatedById":194147,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-01T01:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like to ask for a piece of advice. What security systems for your houses do you guys use? Can you name me several brands that produce quality products, such as fire detectors and motion sensors? I want that to be modern. I mean, I would like to control it remotely and see what is happening in a backyard at the moment. So, it seems I also need cameras. By the way, I have heard about Ajax. So you not if their system worth it? I will be very thankful if you name me at least two companies I can call.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T08:43:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223888282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221606786442\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194147\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MaximilianIV\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/1/2020 at 4:34 AM, MaximilianIV said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way, I have heard about Ajax. So you not if their system worth it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, it works. Ask the dude who hopped over our fence and walked straight into a motion sensor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T11:20:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223888282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221606786442\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194147\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MaximilianIV\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/30/2020 at 8:34 PM, MaximilianIV said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat security systems for your houses do you guys use?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be honest, the best security system I had was a German Shepherd.\u00A0 Very protective dog.\u00A0 If you weren\u0027t on \u0022the list\u0022, you didn\u0027t get in my house.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 You could easily mix that with some surface mounted cameras, and skip the need for installing sensors in windows and doors.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, I do realize that\u0027s not what you are asking for.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"radonek","CreatedById":84077,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T17:42:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my opinion, anything that features remote control is inherently unsecure. Professional hardware with dedicated control channels at least require some effort to break into, but the lowend \u0022enter wifi password and download phone app\u0022 is worse off then key under the mat.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"invision","CreatedById":178900,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T18:43:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\na dog is your best security, it will let you know when crooks,\u00A0squirrels, and leaves from trees are near your property.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T20:55:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndog \u002B shotgun will do wonders. im not a dog person though, so i try to make myself very scary and i never leave so yea good luck steeling my worthless junk.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSaint","CreatedById":70033,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T23:08:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally, I\u0027m in the dog \u002B gun crowd. Mainly because:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607276569\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284077\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022radonek\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, radonek said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my opinion, anything that features remote control is inherently unsecure. Professional hardware with dedicated control channels at least require some effort to break into, but the lowend \u0022enter wifi password and download phone app\u0022 is worse off then key under the mat.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis ^.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be fair, unless your dog is very intimidating, he isn\u0027t going to stop a burglar either. (A sleeping pill wrapped in a slice of ham works wonders. Or so I hear.) But, like anything else in home security, the goal is not to make your home an impenetrable fortress (which is impossible). The goal is to make your home more trouble to break into than the house next door.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"radonek","CreatedById":84077,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-06T23:32:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890367\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607296115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u2026 pill wrapped in a slice of ham works wonders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what our vet said. Our dog had his own opinion in the matter\u00A0:-)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nED:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngun? shotgun? I wonder what kind of postapocalyptic wilderness\u00A0are you guys living in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-06T23:37:31Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2020 11:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by radonek\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lewie","CreatedById":203745,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T02:19:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607297525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284077\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022radonek\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, radonek said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nED:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngun? shotgun? I wonder what kind of postapocalyptic wilderness\u00A0are you guys living in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*bewilderment*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is America....guns (especially shotguns w/ rock salt)\u00A0are popular for home protection.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T02:44:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890401\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607307570\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203745\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lewie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, Lewie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nguns (especially shotguns w/ rock salt)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought flechette rounds were bad...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T05:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. A dog == a mobile server with neural network. Provides only local presence, produces a lot of false positives. Should be virtually emulated and upgraded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Cats repel\u00A0creepers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Did anyone try a celled magpie with a jingle bell? Presumably it should be better than a dog.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890401\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607307570\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203745\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lewie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Lewie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607297525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284077\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022radonek\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, radonek said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nED:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngun? shotgun? I wonder what kind of postapocalyptic wilderness\u00A0are you guys living in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*bewilderment*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is America....guns (especially shotguns w/ rock salt)\u00A0are popular for home protection.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a fence with skulls of previous trespassers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-07T05:59:34Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2020 05:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T09:37:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607297525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284077\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022radonek\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, radonek said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what our vet said. Our dog had his own opinion in the matter\u00A0:-)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nED:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngun? shotgun? I wonder what kind of postapocalyptic wilderness\u00A0are you guys living in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nim from alaska. from the size of some of the wildlife we got (bears, wolves, moose, caribou, sea lions, mosquitoes), im surprised they are not mandatory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607309047\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought flechette rounds were bad...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwillie pete is hard to come by, not impossible mind you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-07T09:37:53Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2020 09:37  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Nuke\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSaint","CreatedById":70033,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T16:01:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890438\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607320759\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a fence with skulls of previous trespassers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure our HOA CC\u0026amp;Rs specifically prohibit this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890401\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607307570\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203745\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lewie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Lewie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(especially shotguns w/ rock salt)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad plan. If you don\u0027t need to respond with lethal force, then don\u0027t shoot. If you do need to respond with lethal force, then why have a less-lethal round in the chamber?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-07T16:02:42Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2020 04:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by TheSaint\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lewie","CreatedById":203745,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T16:10:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607356909\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure our HOA CC\u0026amp;Rs specifically prohibit this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad plan. If you don\u0027t need to respond with lethal force, then don\u0027t shoot. If you do need to respond with lethal force, then why have a less-lethal round in the chamber?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u2019t need to shoot to kill. Even just firing said gun into the air would be enough to make \u2018em scram.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T16:52:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607356909\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure our HOA CC\u0026amp;Rs specifically prohibit this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI understand.\u00A0 Uniform\u00A0design, so on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607356909\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890401\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607307570\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203745\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lewie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Lewie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(especially shotguns w/ rock salt)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad plan. If you don\u0027t need to respond with lethal force, then don\u0027t shoot. If you do need to respond with lethal force, then why have a less-lethal round in the chamber?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe he means salt in pieces, not in powder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890367\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607296115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe goal is to make your home more trouble to break into than the house next door.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd after they start robbing the neighbors, to call police and tell them that the neighbors are under attack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what they name \u0022neighborhood watch\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"costalacosta","CreatedById":208581,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T16:59:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, guys! I like your ideas about guns and dogs. Sound very protective, but, unfortunately, I am not sure it suits me. My little doggy is more likely to open the door to the burglars than to protect myself. She is too friendly. Guns are illegal in the UK, so, I need to do a hard job to find them without a license. Anyway, when I am out, the gun could not shut by itself, lol. I have called Ajax and mentioned the comment from DDE, they laughed. Said it works perfectly, by the way. So, I think it would be better than a gun or a dog! Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spacescifi","CreatedById":197504,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T18:45:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890562\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607360399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208581\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022costalacosta\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, costalacosta said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, guys! I like your ideas about guns and dogs. Sound very protective, but, unfortunately, I am not sure it suits me. My little doggy is more likely to open the door to the burglars than to protect myself. She is too friendly. Guns are illegal in the UK, so, I need to do a hard job to find them without a license. Anyway, when I am out, the gun could not shut by itself, lol. I have called Ajax and mentioned the comment from DDE, they laughed. Said it works perfectly, by the way. So, I think it would be better than a gun or a dog! Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot all dogs are known for being nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRottweilers. German shepherds. Dobermans. Pit bulls.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are yet more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T19:14:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA hysterical chihuahua.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.google.com/url?sa=i\u0026amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwagwalking.com%2Ftraining%2Fnot-be-aggressive\u0026amp;psig=AOvVaw21U4pmV3heL4_ls3dOJC5F\u0026amp;ust=1607455034247000\u0026amp;source=images\u0026amp;cd=vfe\u0026amp;ved=0CAkQjhxqFwoTCJDv0ubKvO0CFQAAAAAdAAAAABAe\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EHow to Train Your Chihuahua Dog to Not Be Aggressive | Wag!\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022How-to-Train-Your-Chihuahua-Dog-to-Not-B\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022116.67\u0022 height=\u0022800\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://images.wagwalkingweb.com/media/training_guides/not-be-aggressive/hero/How-to-Train-Your-Chihuahua-Dog-to-Not-Be-Aggressive.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-07T19:19:41Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2020 07:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T20:37:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere have been situations where house cats have repelled burglars.\u00A0 of course it only takes the cat to not be in a burglar repelling mood at the time for it not to work. there is also the chance that the cat might like the burglar more than you.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spacescifi","CreatedById":197504,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-07T21:41:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607373478\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere have been situations where house cats have repelled burglars.\u00A0 of course it only takes the cat to not be in a burglar repelling mood at the time for it not to work. there is also the chance that the cat might like the burglar more than you.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah...cats have that unpredictabilty factor...which often works in their favor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen it does not...\u0022Cat has nine lives.\u0022\u00A0 saying applies, or\u00A0 \u0022Curiousity killed the cat.\u0022 otherwise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-08T14:00:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223890663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221607373478\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere have been situations where house cats have repelled burglars.\u00A0 of course it only takes the cat to not be in a burglar repelling mood at the time for it not to work. there is also the chance that the cat might like the burglar more than you.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe feline alarm is unlikely to \u0022work\u0022 until the burglar begins to rifle through the closet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-08T14:01:11Z\u0022 title=\u002212/08/2020 02:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 8, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by DDE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ETypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}